You are working on **Vibe Coding Playground** — a visual showcase site for vibe coding (AI-assisted development).

## Project Context
- Read `/docs/PROJECT_OVERVIEW.md` for goals and audience
- Read `/docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for file structure and component specs
- Read `/docs/TECH_STACK.md` for stack decisions and color palette
- Update `/docs/CURRENT_STATUS.md` after completing tasks

## Stack
- Next.js 15, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS v4, Motion (Framer Motion v12)
- Dark theme primary, light theme via `dark:` Tailwind prefix
- Fonts: Syne (display) + DM Sans (body) + JetBrains Mono (code)

## Code Rules
1. Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for all className merging
2. Use Motion variants from `@/lib/animations` — don't create inline variants
3. Every component has typed props interface — no `any`
4. Sections go in `src/components/sections/`
5. Reusable UI goes in `src/components/ui/`
6. Visual effects go in `src/components/effects/`
7. Interactive demos go in `src/components/interactive/`

## Animation Rules
- Use `useInView` from Motion for scroll-triggered animations
- `viewport={{ once: true, margin: "-100px" }}` for section entries
- Always respect `prefers-reduced-motion` via `useReducedMotion` hook
- Stagger delays: 0.1s between children, 0.2s initial delay

## Design Rules
- Dark theme: bg = #080B14, accent = #00F5FF (cyan), secondary = #7C3AED (violet)
- Light theme: bg = #F8F9FF, accent = #0099CC
- Glassmorphism: `backdrop-blur-md bg-white/5 border border-white/10`
- Glow effect: `shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(0,245,255,0.3)]`
- Sections have `py-24 md:py-32` padding
- Max content width: `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8`

## Component Template
```tsx
'use client'

import { motion, useInView } from 'motion/react'
import { useRef } from 'react'
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils'
import { fadeUpVariant, staggerContainer } from '@/lib/animations'

interface ComponentNameProps {
  className?: string
}

export function ComponentName({ className }: ComponentNameProps) {
  const ref = useRef(null)
  const isInView = useInView(ref, { once: true, margin: '-100px' })

  return (
    <motion.div
      ref={ref}
      variants={staggerContainer}
      initial="hidden"
      animate={isInView ? 'visible' : 'hidden'}
      className={cn('', className)}
    >
      {/* content */}
    </motion.div>
  )
}
```
